The paper discusses training convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and proposes a new algorithm called Sparse Weight Activation Training (SWAT) to reduce computational demands and memory footprint. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
